<!-- Experience Patterns -->
<category>
    <pattern>I HAVE * YEARS OF EXPERIENCE</pattern>
    <template>
        <set name="experience_years"><star/></set>
        Nice! <star/> years of experience is great. 
        <condition name="experience_years">
            <li value="1">You're just getting started - that's exciting!</li>
            <li value="2">You're building solid foundations!</li>
            <li value="3">You're developing good expertise!</li>
            <li value="4">You're becoming quite experienced!</li>
            <li value="5">You've got solid mid-level experience!</li>
            <li>You're definitely a seasoned professional!</li>
        </condition>
        What kind of role are you looking for?
    </template>
</category>

<category>
    <pattern>* YEARS EXPERIENCE</pattern>
    <template><srai>I HAVE <star/> YEARS OF EXPERIENCE</srai></template>
</category>

<category>
    <pattern>* YEARS</pattern>
    <template><srai>I HAVE <star/> YEARS OF EXPERIENCE</srai></template>
</category>

<!-- Tech Stack Patterns -->
<category>
    <pattern>I WORK WITH *</pattern>
    <template>
        <set name="tech_stack"><star/></set>
        Impressive! You're working with <star/>. That's a solid tech stack.
        Let me dive deeper with some questions that match your experience.
        
        Here's a technical question for you:
        <random>
            <li>How do you approach debugging complex issues in your applications?</li>
            <li>Tell me about a challenging project you've worked on recently.</li>
            <li>How do you ensure code quality in your development process?</li>
            <li>What's your approach to handling performance optimization?</li>
        </random>
    </template>
</category>

